	  <concept id="i1091276"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">25.703-2</ph> Iran Sanctions Act.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d1660e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1674e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Certification.</p>
					          <ol id="d1660e23" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1674e27" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Certification relating to activities described in section 5 of the Iran Sanctions Act. As required by section 6(b)(1)(A) of the Iran Sanctions Act (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=(title:50%20section:1701%20edition:prelim)%20OR%20(granuleid:USC-prelim-title50-section1701)&amp;f=treesort&amp;edition=prelim&amp;num=0&amp;jumpTo=true"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">50 U.S.C. 1701</xref> note), unless an exception applies in accordance with paragraph (c) of this subsection, or a waiver is granted in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1091310.dita#i1091310"
                              base="i1091310"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">25.703-4</xref>, each offeror must certify that the offeror, and any person owned or controlled by the offeror, does not engage in any activity for which sanctions may be imposed under section 5 of the Iran Sanctions Act. Such activities, which are described in detail in section 5 of the Iran Sanctions Act, relate to the energy sector of Iran and development by Iran of weapons of mass destruction or other military capabilities.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1674e42" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Certification relating to transactions with Iran's Revolutionary Guard Corps. As required by section 6(b)(1)(B) of the Iran Sanctions Act (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=(title:50%20section:1701%20edition:prelim)%20OR%20(granuleid:USC-prelim-title50-section1701)&amp;f=treesort&amp;edition=prelim&amp;num=0&amp;jumpTo=true"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">50 U.S.C. 1701</xref> note), unless an exception applies in accordance with paragraph (c) of this subsection, or a waiver is granted in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1091310.dita#i1091310"
                              base="i1091310"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">25.703-4</xref>, each offeror must certify that the offeror, and any person owned or controlled by the offeror, does not knowingly engage in any significant transaction (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">i.e.</i>, a transaction that exceeds $3,500) with Iran's Revolutionary Guard Corps or any of its officials, agents, or affiliates, the property and interests in property of which are blocked pursuant to the International Emergency Economic Powers Act (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=(title:50%20section:1701%20edition:prelim)%20OR%20(granuleid:USC-prelim-title50-section1701)&amp;f=treesort&amp;edition=prelim&amp;num=0&amp;jumpTo=true"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">50 U.S.C. 1701</xref>
								                <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">et seq</i>.)(see OFACâ€™s Specially Designated Nationals and Blocked Persons List at <xref href="https://www.treasury.gov/resource-center/sanctions/SDN-List/Pages/default.aspx"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">https://www.treasury.gov/resource-center/sanctions/SDN-List/Pages/default.aspx</xref>).</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1674e72" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
						            <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Remedies</i>. Upon the determination of a false certification under paragraph (a) of this subsection, the agency shall take one or more of the following actions:</p>
					          <ol id="d1660e59" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1674e85" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The contracting officer terminates the contract in accordance with procedures in part <xref href="FAR-i1069121.dita#i1069121"
                              base="i1069121"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">49</xref>, or for commercial items, see <xref href="FAR-i1113036.dita#i1113036"
                              base="i1113036"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">12.403</xref>.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1674e100" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The suspending official suspends the contractor in accordance with the procedures in subpart <xref href="FAR-i1115147.dita#i1115147"
                              base="i1115147"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">9.4</xref>.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1674e112" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The debarring official debars the contractor for a period of at least two years in accordance with the procedures in subpart <xref href="FAR-i1115147.dita#i1115147"
                              base="i1115147"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">9.4</xref>.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1674e126" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
						            <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Exception for trade agreements</i>. The certification requirements of paragraph (a) of this subsection do not apply if the acquisition is subject to trade agreements and the offeror certifies that all the offered products are designated country end products or designated country construction material (see subpart <xref href="FAR-i1092400.dita#i1092400"
                        base="i1092400"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">25.4</xref>).</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
